  30. /* [size] is a number of elements for the [to_do.item] array */
  31. ‌static void alloc_todo (caml_domain_state* d, int size)
  32. {
  33.   struct final_todo *result =
  34.     caml_stat_alloc_noexc (sizeof (struct final_todo) +
  35.                            size * sizeof (struct final));
  36.   struct caml_final_info *f = d->final_info;
  37.   if (result == NULL) caml_fatal_error ("out of memory");
  38.   result->next = NULL;
  39.   result->size = size;
  40.   if (f->todo_tail == NULL) {
  41.     f->todo_head = result;
  42.     f->todo_tail = result;
  43.   } else {
  44.     CAMLassert (f->todo_tail->next == NULL);
  45.     f->todo_tail->next = result;
  46.     f->todo_tail = result;
  47.   }
  48. }

  50. /* Find white finalisable values, move them to the finalising set, and
  51.    darken them (if darken_value is true). */
  52. ‌static void generic_final_update
  53.   (caml_domain_state* d, struct finalisable *final, int darken_value)
  54. {
  55.   uintnat i, j, k;
  56.   uintnat todo_count = 0;
  57.   struct caml_final_info *f = d->final_info;

  59.   CAMLassert (final->old <= final->young);
  60.   for (i = 0; i < final->old; i++) {
  61.     CAMLassert (Is_block (final->table[i].val));
  62.     if (is_unmarked (final->table[i].val)) {
  63.       ++ todo_count;
  64.     }
  65.   }

  67.   /** invariant:
  68.       - 0 <= j <= i /\ 0 <= k <= i /\ 0 <= k <= todo_count
  69.       - i : index in final_table, before i all the values are black
  70.       (alive or in the minor heap) or the finalizer have been copied
  71.       in to_do_tl.
  72.       - j : index in final_table, before j all the values are black
  73.       (alive or in the minor heap), next available slot.
  74.       - k : index in to_do_tl, next available slot.
  75.   */
  76.   if (todo_count > 0) {
  77.     caml_set_action_pending(d);
  78.     alloc_todo (d, todo_count);
  79.     j = k = 0;
  80.     for (i = 0; i < final->old; i++){
  81.       CAMLassert (Is_block (final->table[i].val));
  82.       CAMLassert (Tag_val (final->table[i].val) != Forward_tag);
  83.       if (is_unmarked (final->table[i].val)) {
  84.         /** dead */
  85.         f->todo_tail->item[k] = final->table[i];
  86.         if (!darken_value) {
  87.           /* The value is not darken so the finalisation function
  88.              is called with unit not with the value */
  89.           f->todo_tail->item[k].val = Val_unit;
  90.           f->todo_tail->item[k].offset = 0;
  91.         };
  92.         k++;
  93.       } else {
  94.         /** alive */
  95.         final->table[j++] = final->table[i];
  96.       }
  97.     }
  98.     CAMLassert (i == final->old);
  99.     CAMLassert (k == todo_count);
  100.     final->old = j;
  101.     for ( ; i < final->young; i++) {
  102.       final->table[j++] = final->table[i];
  103.     }
  104.     final->young = j;
  105.     f->todo_tail->size = k;
  106.     if (darken_value) {
  107.       for (i = 0; i < k; i++) {
  108.         /* Note that item may already be dark due to multiple entries in
  109.            the final table. */
  110.         caml_darken (d, f->todo_tail->item[i].val, NULL);
  111.       }
  112.     }
  113.   }
  114. }

  116. ‌int caml_final_update_first (caml_domain_state* d)

  142. /* Call the finalisation functions for the finalising set.
  143.    Note that this function must be reentrant.
  144. */
  145. ‌value caml_final_do_calls_exn(void)
  146. {
  147.   struct final f;
  148.   value res;
  149.   struct caml_final_info *fi = Caml_state->final_info;

  151.   if (fi->running_finalisation_function) return Val_unit;
  152.   if (fi->todo_head != NULL) {
  153.     call_timing_hook(&caml_finalise_begin_hook);
  154.     caml_gc_message (0x80, "Calling finalisation functions.\n");
  155.     while (1) {
  156.       while (fi->todo_head != NULL && fi->todo_head->size == 0) {
  157.         struct final_todo *next_head = fi->todo_head->next;
  158.         caml_stat_free (fi->todo_head);
  159.         fi->todo_head = next_head;
  160.         if (fi->todo_head == NULL) fi->todo_tail = NULL;
  161.       }
  162.       if (fi->todo_head == NULL) break;
  163.       CAMLassert (fi->todo_head->size > 0);
  164.       --fi->todo_head->size;
  165.       f = fi->todo_head->item[fi->todo_head->size];
  166.       fi->running_finalisation_function = 1;
  167.       res = caml_callback_exn (f.fun, f.val + f.offset);
  168.       fi->running_finalisation_function = 0;
  169.       if (Is_exception_result(res)) return res;
  170.     }
  171.     caml_gc_message (0x80, "Done calling finalisation functions.\n");
  172.     call_timing_hook(&caml_finalise_end_hook);
  173.   }
  174.   return Val_unit;
  175. }

  180. /* Called my major_gc for marking roots */
  181. ‌void caml_final_do_roots
  182.   (scanning_action act, scanning_action_flags fflags, void* fdata,
  183.    caml_domain_state* d, int do_val)
  184. {
  185.   uintnat i;
  186.   struct final_todo *todo;
  187.   struct caml_final_info *f = d->final_info;

  189.   CAMLassert (f->first.old <= f->first.young);
  190.   for (i = 0; i < f->first.young; i++) {
  191.     Call_action (act, fdata, f->first.table[i].fun);
  192.     if (do_val)
  193.       Call_action (act, fdata, f->first.table[i].val);
  194.   }

  196.   CAMLassert (f->last.old <= f->last.young);
  197.   for (i = 0; i < f->last.young; i++) {
  198.     Call_action (act, fdata, f->last.table[i].fun);
  199.     if (do_val)
  200.       Call_action (act, fdata, f->last.table[i].val);
  201.   }

  203.   for (todo = f->todo_head; todo != NULL; todo = todo->next) {
  204.     for (i = 0; i < todo->size; i++) {
  205.       Call_action (act, fdata, todo->item[i].fun);
  206.       Call_action (act, fdata, todo->item[i].val);
  207.     }
  208.   }
  209. }

  211. /* Called by minor gc for marking roots */
  212. ‌void caml_final_do_young_roots
  213.   (scanning_action act, scanning_action_flags fflags, void* fdata,

  217.   struct caml_final_info *f = d->final_info;

  219.   CAMLassert (f->first.old <= f->first.young);
  220.   for (i = f->first.old; i < f->first.young; i++) {
  221.     Call_action (act, fdata, f->first.table[i].fun);

  225.   CAMLassert (f->last.old <= f->last.old);
  226.   for (i = f->last.old; i < f->last.young; i++) {
  227.     Call_action (act, fdata, f->last.table[i].fun);
  228.     if (do_last_val)
  229.       Call_action (act, fdata, f->last.table[i].val);
  230.   }
  231. }

  233. ‌static void generic_final_minor_update
  234.   (caml_domain_state* d, struct finalisable * final)
  235. {
  236.   uintnat i, j, k;
  237.   uintnat todo_count = 0;
  238.   struct caml_final_info *fi = d->final_info;

  240.   CAMLassert (final->old <= final->young);
  241.   for (i = final->old; i < final->young; i++){
  242.     CAMLassert (Is_block (final->table[i].val));
  243.     if (Is_young(final->table[i].val) &&
  244.         caml_get_header_val(final->table[i].val) != 0){
  245.       ++ todo_count;
  246.     }
  247.   }

  249.   /** invariant:
  250.       - final->old <= j <= i /\ final->old <= k <= i /\ 0 <= k <= todo_count
  251.       - i : index in final_table, before i all the values are alive
  252.             or the finalizer have been copied in to_do_tl.
  253.       - j : index in final_table, before j all the values are alive,
  254.             next available slot.
  255.       - k : index in to_do_tl, next available slot.
  256.   */
  257.   if (todo_count > 0) {
  258.     caml_set_action_pending(d);
  259.     alloc_todo (d, todo_count);
  260.     k = 0;
  261.     j = final->old;
  262.     for (i = final->old; i < final->young; i++) {
  263.       CAMLassert (Is_block (final->table[i].val));
  264.       CAMLassert (Tag_val (final->table[i].val) != Forward_tag);
  265.       if (Is_young(final->table[j].val) &&
  266.           caml_get_header_val(final->table[i].val) != 0) {
  267.         /** dead */
  268.         fi->todo_tail->item[k] = final->table[i];
  269.         /* The finalisation function is called with unit not with the value */
  270.         fi->todo_tail->item[k].val = Val_unit;
  271.         fi->todo_tail->item[k].offset = 0;
  272.         k++;
  273.       } else {
  274.         /** alive */
  275.         final->table[j++] = final->table[i];
  276.       }
  277.     }
  278.     CAMLassert (i == final->young);
  279.     CAMLassert (k == todo_count);
  280.     final->young = j;
  281.     fi->todo_tail->size = todo_count;
  282.   }

  284.   /** update the minor value to the copied major value */
  285.   for (i = final->old; i < final->young; i++) {
  286.     CAMLassert (Is_block (final->table[i].val));
  287.     if (Is_young(final->table[i].val)) {
  288.       CAMLassert (caml_get_header_val(final->table[i].val) == 0);
  289.       final->table[i].val = Field(final->table[i].val, 0);
  290.     }
  291.   }
  292. }

  306. ‌void caml_final_merge_finalisable
  307.   (struct finalisable *source, struct finalisable *target)
  308. {
  309.   uintnat new_size;

  311.   CAMLassert (target->old <= target->young);
  312.   /* to merge the source structure, all its values are in the major heap */
  313.   CAMLassert (source->old == source->young);
  314.   if (target->young + source->young >= target->size) {
  315.     new_size = 2 * (target->young + source->young);
  316.     if (target->table == NULL) {
  317.       target->table = caml_stat_alloc (new_size * sizeof (struct final));
  318.       CAMLassert (target->old == 0);
  319.       CAMLassert (target->young == 0);
  320.       target->size = new_size;
  321.     } else {
  322.       target->table = caml_stat_resize (target->table,
  323.                                        new_size * sizeof (struct final));
  324.       target->size = new_size;
  325.     }
  326.   }
  327.   /* all values from the source are old, we will prepend them
  328.      into the old area of the target */
  329.   memmove(target->table + source->young, target->table,
  330.           target->young * sizeof (struct final));
  331.   memcpy(target->table, source->table,
  332.          source->young * sizeof (struct final));
  333.   /* adjust indices for the prepended values from the source */
  334.   target->old += source->young;
  335.   target->young += source->young;

  337. #ifdef DEBUG
  338.   {
  339.     /** check target is well formed on the values */
  340.     int i;
  341.     for (i = 0; i < target->old; i++) {
  342.       CAMLassert (target->table[i].val); /* no null ptrs */
  343.       CAMLassert (Is_block(target->table[i].val));
  344.       CAMLassert (!Is_young(target->table[i].val));
  345.     };
  346.     for (; i < target->young; i++) {
  347.       CAMLassert (target->table[i].val); /* no null ptrs */
  348.       CAMLassert (Is_block(target->table[i].val));
  349.     }
  350.   }
  351. #endif
  352. }

  354. ‌static void generic_final_register (struct finalisable *final, value f, value v)
  355. {
  356.   uintnat new_size;

  358.   if (!Is_block(v) || Tag_val(v) == Lazy_tag
  359. #ifdef FLAT_FLOAT_ARRAY
  360.       || Tag_val(v) == Double_tag
  361. #endif
  362.       || Tag_val(v) == Forcing_tag
  363.       || Tag_val(v) == Forward_tag) {
  364.     caml_invalid_argument ("Gc.finalise");
  365.   }
  366.   CAMLassert (final->old <= final->young);

  368.   if (final->young >= final->size) {
  369.     if (final->table == NULL) {
  370.       new_size = 30;
  371.       final->table = caml_stat_alloc (new_size * sizeof (struct final));
  372.       CAMLassert (final->old == 0);
  373.       CAMLassert (final->young == 0);
  374.       final->size = new_size;
  375.     } else {
  376.       new_size = final->size * 2;
  377.       final->table = caml_stat_resize (final->table,
  378.                                        new_size * sizeof (struct final));
  379.       final->size = new_size;
  380.     }
  381.   }
  382.   CAMLassert (final->young < final->size);
  383.   final->table[final->young].fun = f;
  384.   if (Tag_val(v) == Infix_tag) {
  385.     final->table[final->young].offset = Infix_offset_val (v);
  386.     final->table[final->young].val = v - Infix_offset_val (v);
  387.   } else {
  388.     final->table[final->young].offset = 0;
  389.     final->table[final->young].val = v;
  390.   }
  391.   ++ final->young;
  392. }
